[[File:Lady Gaga EuroPride 2011 06.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Twitter user  Lady Gaga at Euro Pride in Rome, Italy]]
'''Lady Gaga is on Twitter''', and [[Lady Gaga]] is the site's most popular user, a position she has held for a long time.  She was the first user to acquire 10 million followers.  [[Justin Bieber on Twitter|Justin Bieber Twitter fans]] have started a rivalry with Gaga and her Twitter user base, in their attempt to unseat Gaga from the top position.  She interacts with her fans on Twitter, giving them shout outs while on tour in places like South Korea and Australia. She was in a recent Twitter controversy after using the [[hashtag]] #PopSingersDontEat and making a comment people saw as dismissive of eating disorders.

==Twitter followers==
{{As of|28 March 2012}}, [[Lady Gaga]] is the most popular celebrity on [[Twitter]],<ref name=gaga3/> By November 2010, [[Lady Gaga]] was the most popular celebrity Twitter user, with [[Justin Bieber]] trailing her in second place.<ref name=biebstwit13>{{cite web|last=Vena |first=Jocelyn |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1651843/justin-bieber-hits-6-million-twitter-followers.jhtml |title=Justin Bieber Hits 6 Million Twitter Followers&nbsp;<U+2014> Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV |date=9 November 2010 |accessdate=24 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=biebstwits22>{{cite web|last=Vena |first=Jocelyn |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/articles/1651843/justin-bieber-hits-6-million-twitter-followers.jhtml |title=Justin Bieber Hits 6 Million Twitter Followers&nbsp;<U+2014> Music, Celebrity, Artist News |publisher=MTV |date=9 November 2010 |accessdate=24 April 2012}}</ref> She had over 10 million followers in February 2011,<ref name=gaga12/> and 12 million by early July.<ref name=biebstwit1>{{cite news|title=Justin Bieber : Twitter following reaches 11 million -- singer thanks fans|newspaper=Entertainment Examiner|location=USA|date=14 July 2011 |accessdate=24 April 2012|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:AUNB:EAEN&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=1388F78C2AA461C0&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=1053B823C33F21F9}}</ref> In early January 2012, Gaga became the first person to have 18 million followers on Twitter. In response to this milestone, she said "Can't believe I have 18,000,000 Twitter Monsters, really rad, was just a few years ago I had barely any".<ref name=gaga12>{{cite web|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/entertainment/gagas-followers-take-sheen-off-madges-globe-20120117-1q48t.html |title=Gaga's followers take sheen off Madge's globe |publisher=Canberratimes.com.au |date=17 January 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> In February 2012, her twitter follower count was just short of 19 million.<ref name=gaga9>{{cite web|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/entertainment/music/lady-gaga-all-set-to-have-a-ball-20120208-1rf1j.html |title=Lady Gaga Australian tour |publisher=Canberratimes.com.au |date=9 February 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> On 28 March 2012, Lady Gaga had 21,764,871 followers while Bieber had 19,070,722.<ref name=biebstwits23>{{cite news |author=Tim Kenneally Reuters 7:18 p.m. CDT, 28 March  2012 |newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]] |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/sns-rt-justin-bieber-lady-gagamt1thewrap36616-20120328,0,7289032.story |title=Justin Bieber Vs. Lady Gaga: Fans wage epic war for Twitter dominance |publisher=chicagotribune.com |date=28 March 2012 |accessdate=24 April 2012}}</ref> While she was the most popular person on Twitter, this did not translate to [[Facebook]] where, with 50 million fans, she only ranked as the third most popular individual on Earth.<ref name=gaga3>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/article/323485 |title=Lady Gaga hits the 50,000,000 Facebook Fans mark, but not tops |publisher=Digitaljournal.com |date= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>

==Bieber rivalry==
In March 2012, Bieber fans attempted to unseat Lady Gaga as the most popular celebrity on Twitter. The fan campaign is described by the [[Chicago Tribune]] as a "[[jihad]] against Gaga's Twitter dominance." Bieber's fans managed to make #OperationUnfollowGaga a trending topic on Twitter by mid-March.  The campaign annoyed some Bieber fans, and was not successful.  Neither Bieber nor Lady Gaga discussed their mutual fanbase's campaigns on Twitter.<ref name=biebstwits23>{{cite news |author=Tim Kenneally Reuters 7:18 p.m. CDT, 28 March  2012 |newspaper=[[Chicago Tribune]] |url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/sns-rt-justin-bieber-lady-gagamt1thewrap36616-20120328,0,7289032.story |title=Justin Bieber Vs. Lady Gaga: Fans wage epic war for Twitter dominance |publisher=chicagotribune.com |date=28 March 2012 |accessdate=24 April 2012}}</ref>

==Fan and celebrity interaction==
Lady Gaga gives shout outs to her fans.  Examples of this include an April 2012 shout out when she arrived at [[Gimpo International Airport]], saying "What a warm and exciting welcome to Korea. I missed this country so much. Will be asleep in my castle until rehearsal. I love u!<U+201D><ref name=gaga1>{{cite web|url=http://www.mb.com.ph/articles/357879/lady-gaga-ready-seoul-concert-amid-protests-18-rating |title=Lady Gaga ready for Seoul concert amid protests, 18+ rating &#124; The Manila Bulletin Newspaper Online |publisher=Mb.com.ph |date= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> She made similar tweets surrounding her trip to [[Melbourne, Australia]].<ref name=gaga8>{{cite web|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/entertainment/music/gaga-adds-extra-melbourne-show-20120313-1uxln.html |title=Gaga adds extra Melbourne show |publisher=Canberratimes.com.au |date=13 March 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> She has leaked information about her concert schedule on Twitter.<ref name=gaga9/><ref name=gaga17>{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/music/news/article.cfm?c_id=264&objectid=10784348 |title=Lady Gaga confirms 'spectacular' Auckland concert&nbsp;<U+2014> Music&nbsp;<U+2014> NZ Herald News |publisher=Nzherald.co.nz |date= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> [[Madonna]] has given Gaga a shoutout on Twitter, say "I applaud Lady Gaga support of the gay community and her commitment to stop bullying."<ref name=gaga10>{{cite web|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/entertainment/music/cyber-madge-for-a-limited-time-only-20120327-1vwco.html |title=Madonna Joins Twitter&#124; MDNA&#124; #Askmadonna&#124; Justin Bieber |publisher=Canberratimes.com.au |date=27 March 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>

==Twitter content==
On Twitter, Gaga has suggested parents should take responsibility for what material their children are exposed to.<ref name=gaga1/>  She has expressed her love of [[Britney Spears]] on Twitter.  One Spears centric tweet said "Real fans never turn their back on you #WillAlwaysLoveBritney Some stars really are as sweet as you thought they were."<ref name=gaga7>{{cite web|author=Loading... |url=http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/73898/Lady-Gaga-And-Britney-Spears-In-Twitter-Lovefest |title=Lady Gaga And Britney Spears In Twitter Lovefest&nbsp;<U+2014> Celebrity Gossip, News & Photos, Movie Reviews, Competitions |publisher=Entertainmentwise |date=19 April 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>  She posted her 2012 [[New Year's Resolution]] on Twitter: "Never be afraid to be kicked in the teeth. Let the blood and the bruises define your legacy."<ref name=gaga12/>

==Controversy and mishaps==
There have been false reports of Gaga's death on Twitter.  At least one of these reports was made by a [[Tim Watson]] imposter.<ref name=gaga5>{{cite news|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/more-news/tim-watson-slams-sick-twitter-impostor-who-claimed-alex-jesaulenko-and-jimmy-bartel-were-dead/story-fn7x8me2-1226334009371 |title=Tim Watson Slams Sick Twitter Imposter |publisher=Herald Sun |location=Melbourne, Australia |date= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref> In April 2012, using the [[hashtag]] #PopSingersDontEat, Gaga tweeted "Just killed back to back spin classes. Eating a salad dreaming of a cheeseburger."  Some people on Twitter thought this comment was insensitive to people with eating disorders and called her out on this.  Other people on Twitter thought the whole thing was blown out of proportion and Tweeted their support of the singer.  The Twitter controversy extended to the [[blogosphere]] with [[National Eating Disorders Association]] making a blog post to weigh in on the situation.  The tweet was also mentioned at a [[Los Angeles]] area conference.<ref name=gaga2>{{cite web|url=http://au.news.yahoo.com/thewest/a/-/world/13419158/lady-gaga-stirs-up-twitter-with-popsingersdonteat/ |title=Lady Gaga stirs up Twitter with #PopSingersDontEat&nbsp;<U+2014> The West Australian |publisher=Au.news.yahoo.com |date=14 April 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=gaga4>{{cite web|author=By Reuters |url=http://tribune.com.pk/story/365175/lady-gaga-stirs-up-twitter/ |title=Lady Gaga stirs up Twitter&nbsp;<U+2013> The Express Tribune |publisher=Tribune.com.pk |date=15 April 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=gaga12>{{cite web|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2012-04-13/entertainment/sns-rt-us-ladygaga-cheeseburgerbre83d00i-20120413_1_lady-gaga-hash-tag-tweet |title=Lady Gaga stirs up Twitter with #PopSingersDontEat&nbsp;<U+2014> Chicago Tribune |publisher=Articles.chicagotribune.com |date=13 April 2012 |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>

[[Amy Winehouse]]'s father used Twitter to address rumours that Gaga would portray his daughter in a movie.  One of his Tweets on the subject said, "I never said Lady Gaga will play Amy in film. Also Amy's room not a shrine. Wot a load of rubbish."<ref name=gaga18>{{cite web|author=Blogger Bites Back |url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/entertainment/news/article.cfm?c_id=1501119&objectid=10773142 |title=Gaga to play Winehouse? Not true, dad says&nbsp;<U+2014> Entertainment&nbsp;<U+2014> NZ Herald News |publisher=Nzherald.co.nz |date= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=gaga19>{{cite web|first=Mitch|last=Winehouse|url=https://twitter.com/#!/mitchwinehouse/status/146384098913554434|publisher=Twitter|title=I never said Lady Gaga will play Amy in film. Also Amy's room not a shrine. Wot a load of rubbish.|date=13 December 2011|accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>

==Tech and public relations industry==
Technology journalists cite Lady Gaga's Twitter popularity as an example of the potential reach that products based on Twitter can achieve.<ref name=gaga4>{{cite web|url=http://www.techflash.com/seattle/2012/04/chirpify-launches-twitter-payment-system.html |title=Chirpify launches Twitter payments, gets $1.3M investment |publisher=Techflash.com |date= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=gaga17>{{cite web|url=http://www.nzherald.co.nz/technology/news/article.cfm?c_id=5&objectid=10792027 |title=Spotify set to stream into NZ&nbsp;<U+2014> Technology&nbsp;<U+2014> NZ Herald News |publisher=Nzherald.co.nz |date= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>  Gaga's popularity has also been used in police training for social media usage in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref name=gaga6>{{cite web|url=http://news.stv.tv/scotland/west-central/304667-scottish-police-force-reveals-plan-for-134-officers-to-tweet-while-on-duty/ |title=Police officers set to tweet on the beat with own Twitter accounts &#124; Glasgow and West &#124; STV News |publisher=News.stv.tv |date= |accessdate=25 April 2012}}</ref>

